The paper focuses on the task of automatic image retrieval for historical handwritten documents, which involves computer vision (CV) and information retrieval (IR) techniques. The use of large image data sets and the investigation of performance suggest a focus on deep learning (DL) and natural language processing (NLP) methods, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV), information retrieval (cs.IR), and deep learning (cs.DL). The task of writer retrieval also suggests a potential focus on natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (cs.CL), while the use of multiple methods and the competition aspect suggest a potential focus on machine learning (cs.LG).
